headline: Exxon Mobil to cut nearly 400 jobs in Texas, filing says
summary: DENVER (Reuters) -Exxon Mobil will cut nearly 400 jobs in Texas following its purchase of shale producer Pioneer Natural Resources, according to a regulatory filing.  The company will cut 376 jobs in Irving, Texas, and 18 workers in Midland, according to the filing with the Texas Workforce Commission.  About 1,900 Pioneer employees were offered jobs as part of the merger, and a majority of those accepted their offers, the filing said.
